<div style="padding-left:2%;padding-right:2%;">



 <p>Are you the urban dweller who constantly dreams of growing their own fresh herbs and harvesting plump tomatoes, but donâ€™t have the space to?<b> The rooftop garden</b> is a perfect solution for you! This method utilizes wasted space, while also adding a fun and decorative vibe! <a href = "https://www.bhg.com/gardening/landscaping-projects/landscape-basics/balcony-and-rooftop-gardening/?">Here</a> are some design ideas to get you started!
<br>
<p>There are two main types of gardens you could set up:

<br><b><i><u>1. Container Gardens: </i></b></u>
   <ul style="line-height:200%">
	<li><b>Easy to DIY!</b> Use anything from old Tupperware boxes to wooden baskets as planters! <a href ="https://www.pinterest.com/hometalk/container-gardening/">Click here</a> to see some fun ideas.
	<li>Often <b>cost less, anywhere between $500-$1000</b> for installation and maintenance.For more budgeting tips, <a href="https://www.simple.com/blog/budget-to-build-and-maintain-an-urban-rooftop-garden">click here. </a>
	<li>When considering what fits your space and budget the best, <b>check out your local gardening center</b> first. Chances are, they have pre-made planters and can advise you on specifics like location, installations and free design tips!  Click here to learn more about space and other installation conditions.

 </ul>

<br><b><i><u>2. Green Roof Gardens: </i></b></u>
   <ul style="line-height:200%">
	<li>For the gardener willing to go all out, consider the green roof garden. It is a more complex layout for gardening which <b>involves converting the entire rooftop into a structural system</b> which can support plant insulation, drainage and plant growth mediums.
	<li>Always <b>contact a licensed professional to check out the structural integrity of your building</b> first, and get the green signal to go green! Check out <a href ="https://www.gardeningknowhow.com/special/urban/gardening-laws.htm">this website</a> for more information on gardening laws and licenses you might require before implementing green roofs.
	<li>Green roof gardens cost anywhere from <b>$30 per sq.ft. to $200 per sq.ft</b>, but if installed properly, can <b>enhance the lifespan of a conventional roof by almost 20 years!</b> Want more information on costs? <a href ="https://www.doityourself.com/stry/estimating-the-cost-of-a-rooftop-garden">Click here</a> to find out.

   </ul>
<br>
<p><b><i>Some advantages of maintaining a roof garden in your home:</b></i>
<ul style="line-height:200%">
<li>It reduces carbon dioxide emission while increasing oxygen levels.
<li>It reduces heat emission in the building, lowering energy costs.
<li>It conserves water by capturing and harvesting rainwater and also by preventing stormwater runoff.
</ul>



